HEADWORD: Cresselle
<hw>Cres*selle"</hw> <pr>(kr?s-s?l")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>cr⟦eacute⟧celle</ets> rattle.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A
wooden rattle sometimes used as a substitute for a bell, in the Roman
Catholic church, during the latter part of Holy Week, or the last week
of Lent.</def>⟦br⟧
